<p>The US Coast Guard shared photos taken outside its station in Venice, Louisiana, showing a massive alligator swimming outside the partially flooded facility during the storm.  </p>

<p>On Thursday, the National Hurricane Center warned that a new tropical depression - dubbed depression 22 - formed in the southwestern Gulf of Mexico. </p>

<p>Forecasters said the depression could become Tropical Storm Alpha as it moves slowly over the western Gulf during the next few days. The storm is projected to slow down and turn west toward the Texas Gulf Coast. It could turn into a hurricane by Sunday. </p>

<p>Meanwhile, Hurricane Teddy strengthened to a powerful Category 4 storm in the Atlantic. The storm currently poses no threat to land.  </p>
